$\triangle ABC$ is a right triangle, since $9^2 + 12^2 = 15^2$. Thus, $\angle ABC = 90^\circ$.

[asy]
unitsize(0.3 cm);

pair A, B, C, D;

A = (0,9);
B = (0,0);
C = (12,0);
D = (0,4);

draw(A--B--C--cycle);
draw(C--D);

label("$A$", A, NW);
label("$B$", B, SW);
label("$C$", C, SE);
label("$D$", D, W);
